WEBVTT

00:01.876 --> 00:03.378
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

00:05.338 --> 00:10.135
RYAN: So, I'm in turmoil,
and I have a grudge to bear,

00:10.218 --> 00:11.594
but I've got loads of passion.

00:11.678 --> 00:13.722
-You're not
taking this seriously.
-(CHUCKLING)

00:13.805 --> 00:15.515
Anyway, it might
not be about you.

00:15.598 --> 00:17.851
The cards haven't yet
revealed their subject.

00:17.934 --> 00:19.185
-Ooh.
-(CHUCKLING)

00:21.229 --> 00:23.273
Wow. Jesus, Ryan,
what did you put in that?

00:23.356 --> 00:25.275
RYAN: We didn't
have any vermouth,
so I used grappa.

00:25.358 --> 00:28.778
We didn't have any tonic,
so I used grapefruit juice.

00:28.862 --> 00:31.239
-I think it's zesty.
-Okay.

00:32.615 --> 00:33.992
Knight of Wands.

00:37.412 --> 00:40.165
Ready for battle
and full of fire, but it's
upside down, so it's reversed.

00:40.248 --> 00:41.916
What does that mean?

00:42.000 --> 00:45.003
Er, he has feelings
for someone that
he's keeping hidden,

00:45.086 --> 00:46.629
and these are
frustrating him.

00:46.713 --> 00:48.673
He needs to
unburden himself
before he causes pain.

00:49.466 --> 00:50.592
Is it about me?

00:50.675 --> 00:51.968
Probably.

00:52.052 --> 00:54.304
Or a father,
or a male friend,
a brother.

00:56.014 --> 00:57.349
Sorry, I didn't mean...

00:59.517 --> 01:02.937
Okay, let's do
the next card.
This is his destiny.

01:04.522 --> 01:06.107
RYAN: Death.
That's all I need.

01:11.696 --> 01:12.697
Damn it!

01:15.200 --> 01:16.826
(SCREAMING)

01:18.119 --> 01:20.538
-Hold still! Hold still!
-Ryan! Oh!

01:22.916 --> 01:24.459
-MOLLY: Thank you.
-Are you all right?

01:24.542 --> 01:26.503
Yeah, I just...
(GROANS)

01:26.585 --> 01:28.546
Why don't you run that
under some cold water
or something?

01:29.047 --> 01:30.173
Okay.

01:36.930 --> 01:38.723
Ryan, what the hell
are you doing?

01:38.806 --> 01:40.725
Playing with tarot here
is like sending
a distress signal

01:40.809 --> 01:42.644
to every weird spirit
in the building.

02:24.269 --> 02:25.437
(SIGHS)

02:47.459 --> 02:49.001
(DIALLING)

02:49.085 --> 02:51.171
(RINGING TONE)

02:51.254 --> 02:53.256
WOMAN:
Hello, Emergency Services.

02:55.967 --> 02:56.968
Hello?

03:16.654 --> 03:17.697
(LOCKER BEEPS)

03:23.578 --> 03:25.789
-Well, maybe
the candle fell over.
-Do you reckon?

03:32.420 --> 03:33.963
What's going on?

03:34.047 --> 03:36.633
A small accident
with a candle
in Molly's room.

03:36.716 --> 03:38.718
Oh, Jesus, Moll.

03:38.802 --> 03:41.680
What have I told you
about burning those stupid
hippy candles in your room?

03:41.763 --> 03:43.098
Don't think
I won't charge you
for the damage.

03:43.181 --> 03:44.683
Kate, Molly was burnt.

03:49.437 --> 03:50.438
Are you all right?

03:51.022 --> 03:52.023
Yeah.

04:09.582 --> 04:12.127
You know, you're pretty much
a nightmare to live with
at the moment, Kate.

04:12.919 --> 04:14.295
What's it to you?

04:14.379 --> 04:16.464
I live here, too.

04:16.548 --> 04:20.635
If this is
about me and you,
it was a mistake.

04:26.016 --> 04:27.434
Let's just pretend
it never happened.

04:31.438 --> 04:32.939
But it did, though,
didn't it?

04:37.652 --> 04:39.154
Just leave it, Jed.

04:45.243 --> 04:46.369
Fine.

04:49.205 --> 04:50.373
(DOOR OPENS)

05:03.011 --> 05:05.013
(DOOR CLOSES)

05:05.096 --> 05:07.849
I can't believe
how moody
Kate is being.

05:07.932 --> 05:12.020
Don't worry about her,
I'll say it was my idea.

05:12.103 --> 05:15.482
Sometimes I think you're
the only person around here
who actually cares.

05:17.233 --> 05:18.610
You okay now?

05:18.693 --> 05:20.570
Yeah, I think
I just need
to get some sleep.

05:24.657 --> 05:25.867
(MOLLY SIGHS)

06:26.094 --> 06:29.889
WOMAN ON TV: There's piles
of this stuff leaching out
from every corner,

06:29.973 --> 06:33.685
Lily, you've got to get
a move on if you want
to sell this house,

06:33.768 --> 06:34.811
tidy up.

06:34.894 --> 06:36.813
I've been getting
text messages.

06:38.898 --> 06:41.526
That's why
I came back here.

06:41.609 --> 06:45.613
I kept getting
this message saying,
"Save Kate."

06:45.697 --> 06:47.407
Who from?

06:47.490 --> 06:51.161
(SIGHING)
I don't know, it's weird.
A four-digit number.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.788
But it's like I don't get
the full message, like,

06:53.872 --> 06:55.498
it doesn't
come through right.

06:57.625 --> 07:00.545
-"Kate dad danger"?
-Yeah.

07:01.546 --> 07:02.756
What do you think?

07:04.591 --> 07:06.301
RYAN: 2-4-3-9?

07:36.414 --> 07:37.916
I only just found this.

07:41.086 --> 07:42.379
I think it's your mum.

07:45.173 --> 07:46.299
What?

07:49.344 --> 07:50.553
Are you sure?

07:50.637 --> 07:52.305
It was in Grace's file.

07:56.393 --> 07:57.435
JED: 2-4-3-9.

07:58.520 --> 08:01.231
Yeah.

08:01.314 --> 08:05.318
RYAN: On this map
of the old hospital, I think
this is the empty ward, 2439.

08:09.698 --> 08:11.281
I need to go
and take a look.

08:11.366 --> 08:12.534
-Do you want me
to come with you?
-No, no, no.

08:15.370 --> 08:16.663
I'd rather go alone.

09:45.126 --> 09:46.586
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

10:58.199 --> 11:00.160
(POP MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)

11:03.788 --> 11:05.206
-MOLLY: Mmm.
-RYAN: Scrambled eggs,

11:05.290 --> 11:07.417
next to the rye bread,
not on it,

11:07.500 --> 11:09.502
grilled tomatoes
and mushrooms.
How's that?

11:10.503 --> 11:12.422
Perfect.
How did you remember?

11:12.505 --> 11:15.633
You're gonna make
someone an amazing
husband one day.

11:15.717 --> 11:17.761
-How you feeling?
-Much better.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.221
I think I just
needed to get
a good night's sleep.

11:23.516 --> 11:25.018
Who writes
letters anymore?

11:25.101 --> 11:26.603
It's my old
school friend, Moon.

11:26.686 --> 11:27.937
She's just had a baby.

11:28.021 --> 11:31.107
-Moon?
-Yeah, her parents
were proper hippies.

11:31.191 --> 11:33.193
Anyway,
it's a really sweet story.

11:33.276 --> 11:35.070
She was totally
unlucky in love

11:35.153 --> 11:38.114
until she realised that
the love of her life was
her best friend, Tom.

11:38.198 --> 11:40.325
Just woke up one day
and realised.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.702
They're married now,
and they live in
a gorgeous cottage,

11:42.786 --> 11:44.788
and they've got
a lovely little baby girl.

11:44.871 --> 11:47.374
Such a good idea,
marrying your friend.

11:47.457 --> 11:49.000
Far less hassle.

11:49.084 --> 11:50.335
Pass the ketchup.

11:53.046 --> 11:55.298
I'd love to live
in the country.

11:55.382 --> 11:57.133
Lucky enough
to get out of here.

12:01.596 --> 12:03.431
WARREN: Why are you
still fretting about
that missing girl?

12:03.515 --> 12:05.308
KATE: Just feel that
maybe something terrible
happened to her

12:05.392 --> 12:07.769
-while she was
under our roof.
-We don't know that.

12:07.852 --> 12:09.604
No one knows
what happened.

12:09.688 --> 12:12.148
You don't have to feel guilty,
we only own the place.

12:14.359 --> 12:17.737
Builders were saying
they reckon someone saw her
get into a white van.

12:18.530 --> 12:19.823
Why didn't you tell me?

12:19.906 --> 12:21.741
It's only pub chat.

12:21.825 --> 12:24.577
They haven't traced it
or anything,
so who knows if it's true?

13:42.447 --> 13:43.656
(HINGES CREAKING)

13:51.247 --> 13:52.374
Do you wanna go out?

13:53.500 --> 13:55.335
You need to get out,
and so do I.

13:56.670 --> 13:58.213
I'm all right.

13:58.296 --> 14:01.424
We don't have to talk
about anything heavy,
just hang out.

14:02.884 --> 14:04.761
-KATE: How's the arm?
-It's pretty minor.

14:04.844 --> 14:06.554
I'm sorry for being
such a bitch.

14:06.638 --> 14:08.807
Did you
just say sorry?

14:08.890 --> 14:12.185
For one night only, missy.
Enjoy it while it lasts.

14:19.317 --> 14:22.487
WARREN: All right, girls?
Where you off to?

14:22.570 --> 14:24.114
KATE: Just going out
for a drink.

14:26.700 --> 14:27.826
KATE: Come on, Moll,
let's go.

14:32.914 --> 14:34.124
You all right, Molly?

14:36.251 --> 14:38.253
(SCREAMING)

14:40.839 --> 14:41.923
Molly?

14:43.550 --> 14:47.512
I must be freaking out
after that burn,
but that was so weird.

14:50.515 --> 14:53.018
I'm sorry,
I didn't take the accident
more seriously.

14:54.519 --> 14:56.646
Must have really
shaken you up.

14:56.730 --> 14:58.481
I didn't think it had.

14:58.565 --> 15:00.567
Ryan, can I have
a word with you?

15:02.444 --> 15:03.528
Okay.

15:07.532 --> 15:10.368
In 1979,
there was a fire
in the asylum,

15:10.452 --> 15:12.245
nearly burned
the place down.

15:12.328 --> 15:14.914
There were three people
who died.

15:14.998 --> 15:17.334
And it was started
deliberately by one
of the patients.

15:17.417 --> 15:18.960
Do you know
who it was?

15:19.044 --> 15:22.339
No, but the sooner
we find out,
the better for Molly.

15:29.763 --> 15:31.681
(RUSTLING FOOTSTEPS)

15:52.744 --> 15:54.245
(MOANS)

16:09.636 --> 16:11.096
(SCREAMING)

16:16.976 --> 16:19.020
I've never had
nightmares like this.

16:20.605 --> 16:23.942
Maybe you need a break.
Go away for a few days.

16:24.025 --> 16:27.570
No. I need to get over it.
I'm being silly.

16:27.654 --> 16:29.489
You're not being silly.
It's serious.

16:30.990 --> 16:32.909
I feel terrible.

16:32.992 --> 16:35.870
Why? You haven't
done anything.

16:40.417 --> 16:41.835
I love you, Moll.

16:43.211 --> 16:45.714
I don't want to see
anything bad
happen to you.

16:46.548 --> 16:47.632
Ever.

17:03.314 --> 17:05.442
You and your pa,
posh lunch.

17:05.525 --> 17:08.319
I've made a reservation,
and I won't take no
for an answer.

17:18.579 --> 17:20.373
Thanks for
the posh nosh.

17:21.915 --> 17:24.669
Thought we'd take
a trip down memory lane.

17:24.752 --> 17:27.005
KATE: Fish and chips
in the park after school.

17:28.048 --> 17:30.467
Used to watch you play
on the swings.

17:30.550 --> 17:33.762
Sit here marvelling
at the passing of time.

17:33.845 --> 17:36.931
You growing up so quickly.
(SIGHING)

17:37.015 --> 17:38.433
Look at you now.

17:40.352 --> 17:41.728
I'm proud of you, love.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.356
I know I don't
tell you often.

17:45.357 --> 17:48.234
No, you don't.

17:50.444 --> 17:52.780
I'm not good at
the emotional stuff.

17:52.864 --> 17:55.241
You needed
a mother for that,

17:55.325 --> 17:57.535
and I know
how hard it was
not having her around.

18:01.790 --> 18:03.291
Why don't we
ever talk about her?

18:03.375 --> 18:06.378
What's the point?
She left.

18:07.462 --> 18:09.005
You don't need reminding.

18:10.465 --> 18:12.175
Why didn't she
keep in touch?

18:12.759 --> 18:14.052
I've no idea.

18:18.765 --> 18:20.266
She left both of us.

18:21.559 --> 18:23.561
You think
I haven't always
wondered why?

18:24.896 --> 18:26.523
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

18:30.860 --> 18:34.614
Are you okay?
You seem out of sorts.

18:34.698 --> 18:38.743
I know living back
in the building maybe
has brought up memories.

18:38.827 --> 18:40.078
Too right it has.

18:41.538 --> 18:43.915
What was it
really like, Dad?

18:43.998 --> 18:46.376
You must know
the stories I've heard.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.503
So many terrible things
went on there.

18:48.586 --> 18:52.007
I know.
They did. They really did.

18:52.090 --> 18:54.217
I never...
If I could have changed
one thing,

18:54.300 --> 18:57.387
I would have
acted sooner to stop it.

18:57.470 --> 19:00.056
I regret that so much.
I want you to know that.

19:04.811 --> 19:06.813
Your grandfather was, um...

19:09.941 --> 19:11.234
He was a complex man.

19:12.986 --> 19:15.238
I'm not sure I'd say
he was a kind man.

19:15.321 --> 19:16.906
Certainly not
as a father.

19:19.701 --> 19:21.661
That's why
I wanted to come back.

19:22.871 --> 19:26.041
Do something good
with the place.

19:26.124 --> 19:29.836
We're not doing a bad job,
are we, you and me?

19:34.966 --> 19:37.927
RYAN: One of the Bedlam
inmates all those years ago
was Michael Pearson,

19:38.011 --> 19:41.514
who burnt down
his family home in 1977,

19:41.598 --> 19:44.684
killing his father,
his mother, his sister,
and the sister's boyfriend.

19:48.480 --> 19:50.023
"His sister's body
was so badly burnt,

19:50.106 --> 19:52.150
"they had to use
dental records
to identify it."

19:52.233 --> 19:53.777
Yeah, he killed her,
and then,
set the body alight.

19:53.860 --> 19:55.320
That's why
the house burnt down.

19:55.403 --> 19:57.864
Why would someone
want to do that
to their own sister?

19:57.947 --> 20:01.409
I don't know.
He'd moved out
a few weeks previously.

20:01.493 --> 20:04.245
Maybe he just
hated his family.

20:04.329 --> 20:05.830
Maybe he was
just a nutter.

20:06.998 --> 20:09.167
No one's
just a nutter, Ryan.

20:23.473 --> 20:24.516
Dad.

20:25.475 --> 20:27.060
Hmm?

20:27.143 --> 20:28.937
I found
something quite odd.

20:36.319 --> 20:37.320
(LOCKER BEEPS)

20:54.004 --> 20:55.714
This belonged to Zoe.

20:56.798 --> 20:58.466
Where was it?

20:58.550 --> 21:00.051
In the incinerator,
after you burned
a load of stuff.

21:00.135 --> 21:03.763
What?
Why didn't you tell me?

21:03.847 --> 21:04.889
I didn't know
what to think.

21:06.182 --> 21:07.183
What do you mean?

21:09.394 --> 21:12.022
Kate, you don't think
I had anything to do
with that girl going missing?

21:13.565 --> 21:14.566
Kate?

21:16.401 --> 21:19.446
I don't know.
I mean, what's it
doing in there?

21:19.529 --> 21:20.947
Give it to the police,
and they can find out.

21:21.031 --> 21:22.532
It's a crucial piece
of evidence.

21:22.615 --> 21:25.243
That girl might be
lying dead somewhere.

21:25.326 --> 21:27.537
Jesus, Kate,
I can't believe
you'd think that!

21:27.620 --> 21:30.707
I'm sorry, Dad.
I wasn't thinking straight.

21:30.790 --> 21:32.125
(SIGHS)

21:35.754 --> 21:36.963
Come here.

21:46.139 --> 21:47.724
You need to take that
to the police.

21:51.603 --> 21:52.645
You do it.

21:58.985 --> 22:00.028
(SIGHS)

22:11.164 --> 22:14.125
WARREN: I hope
you're not keeping Jed
from his work, Ryan?

22:18.546 --> 22:20.382
Lots of history
in this stuff.

22:21.383 --> 22:22.926
Different times, then.

22:23.009 --> 22:24.844
Do you want to see
how it worked?

22:26.096 --> 22:27.138
Eh?

22:27.222 --> 22:28.640
No, I'm all right.

22:28.723 --> 22:30.392
Sit down.

22:30.475 --> 22:32.769
Go on.
It's only a chair.

22:35.313 --> 22:38.983
WARREN: You see,
if you had a patient
that was physically strong,

22:41.111 --> 22:42.946
prone to violence,

22:43.029 --> 22:44.531
you needed to
restrain them first.

22:46.074 --> 22:47.742
RYAN: You know,
I don't think
this is a good idea.

22:47.826 --> 22:50.203
Then, you were free
to examine
their troubled minds,

22:52.789 --> 22:54.249
and do whatever
was necessary.

22:54.332 --> 22:56.042
I'm actually
mildly claustrophobic.

22:58.128 --> 23:00.755
-Oh dear.
It seems to be stuck.
-Warren!

23:00.839 --> 23:03.717
-Really...
-Oh, no! My mistake.

23:05.260 --> 23:06.594
No harm done.

23:10.432 --> 23:11.975
-Hi.
-Hey.

23:16.312 --> 23:17.605
(KATE SIGHS)

23:18.815 --> 23:20.442
What's brought this on?

23:20.525 --> 23:22.277
Well, I read that
cooking was therapeutic.

23:22.360 --> 23:26.197
So, tonight,
everybody's having
the Molly Special.

23:26.281 --> 23:29.659
-Which is?
-Pesto quiche.

23:29.743 --> 23:32.412
You know,
pesto and quiche
aren't friends.

23:32.495 --> 23:35.665
-They're not even
on speaking terms.
-This is very tasty.

23:35.749 --> 23:37.542
I reserve the right
to order pizza.

23:39.753 --> 23:41.838
-What's this?
-Oh, give me that.

23:41.921 --> 23:44.132
A cottage
by the sea?

23:44.215 --> 23:46.259
You're not thinking
of moving out, are you?

23:46.343 --> 23:48.428
It's just an idle thought.

23:48.511 --> 23:50.513
Ryan and I
would like to live
together sometime.

23:50.597 --> 23:51.890
You already live together.

23:53.600 --> 23:55.518
Aah. Okay, okay.

23:55.602 --> 23:57.729
Is this like
your two friends
who just got married

23:57.812 --> 23:59.522
and moved
to a little cottage?

23:59.606 --> 24:02.275
You and Ryan.
Mr and Mrs McAllister?

24:02.859 --> 24:03.985
(KATE CHUCKLES)

24:04.069 --> 24:06.071
You do know
he's gay, right?

24:06.154 --> 24:09.240
Really?
So why hasn't he
come out, then?

24:09.324 --> 24:13.411
Okay, he is sensitive
and in touch with his
feminine side, but so what?

24:13.495 --> 24:14.954
Maybe he is
attracted to boys,

24:15.038 --> 24:18.375
but sexuality is
a sliding scale,
and love is just love.

24:18.458 --> 24:20.377
Don't make a fool
out of yourself, Moll.

24:20.460 --> 24:23.838
So, what, no one else is
allowed to have a relationship
because you're single?

24:23.922 --> 24:25.632
You're the last person
I'd take advice from.

24:27.342 --> 24:28.635
(KATE SIGHS)

24:29.636 --> 24:31.596
(POP MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS)

24:38.395 --> 24:40.980
The coroner's report
on Michael Pearson's victims.

24:53.910 --> 24:56.329
"Remains of petrol found
on Deborah Pearson's body

24:56.413 --> 24:59.457
"indicate it was used
as an accelerant."

24:59.541 --> 25:01.793
(SIGHING)
Tell us something
we don't know.

25:01.876 --> 25:03.503
It wasn't what he used,
it's where he poured it.

25:05.505 --> 25:07.841
-What do you mean?
-He's a coroner.

25:07.924 --> 25:10.427
This stuff was never
in the press.

25:10.510 --> 25:14.597
When they found
Deborah's body, her entire
lower half was burnt away.

25:14.681 --> 25:16.182
That's where
he set her alight.

25:18.143 --> 25:19.352
Jesus.

25:21.229 --> 25:23.064
(SIGHS) Okay, so...

25:23.148 --> 25:27.110
So, there's loads of forensics
data that's been pulled
together on this.

25:27.193 --> 25:29.738
It's consistent in
almost all the cases.

25:29.821 --> 25:32.490
When a man does this
to a woman,

25:32.574 --> 25:35.035
the killing
is sexually motivated.

25:35.118 --> 25:36.745
Yeah, but it was
his sister.

25:36.828 --> 25:38.580
He was sick enough
to set her alight.

25:38.663 --> 25:40.623
He's hardly the man
who's gonna worry about
crossing the line.

25:40.707 --> 25:42.834
Well, so you think
he was trying to
sleep with her?

25:42.917 --> 25:45.420
I think it could be
the reason why
he's fixated on Molly.

25:49.841 --> 25:53.386
Ryan, he thinks
Molly is Deborah.

26:01.394 --> 26:02.479
(FIRE CRACKLING)

26:26.503 --> 26:27.879
(SCREAMING)
Ryan!

26:29.339 --> 26:30.507
Ryan!

26:32.133 --> 26:33.551
(COUGHING)

26:34.344 --> 26:36.012
Ryan!

26:36.096 --> 26:37.597
(COUGHING)

26:39.307 --> 26:40.600
Ryan!

26:42.602 --> 26:43.770
Ryan!

26:46.815 --> 26:48.149
(BREATH TREMBLING)

26:48.233 --> 26:49.901
-What is it?
-I don't know.

26:49.984 --> 26:53.113
I don't know,
it was so horrible.
I was so scared.

27:03.873 --> 27:04.874
(SIGHS)

27:54.341 --> 27:56.176
I thought
I was gonna die.

27:58.219 --> 27:59.721
It was so real.

28:02.307 --> 28:05.727
What you're feeling
is as real as anything.

28:11.024 --> 28:13.276
I think I should probably
try and get some sleep.

28:16.196 --> 28:17.822
If you'd like,
I'll stay here.

28:22.077 --> 28:23.411
You don't have to.

28:24.579 --> 28:25.747
I want to.

28:26.414 --> 28:27.624
Really?

28:30.085 --> 28:31.252
Thank you.

28:32.128 --> 28:33.713
It's for me
as much as you.

28:35.173 --> 28:36.800
Think I'd be happy
leaving you?

30:54.729 --> 30:55.855
Kate, go.

30:57.524 --> 30:58.775
I said go! Now!

31:04.280 --> 31:05.657
(GASPS)

31:05.740 --> 31:06.908
(SHUDDERS)

31:15.417 --> 31:16.626
(MOBILE BEEPS)

31:25.135 --> 31:26.803
(MOBILE BEEPS)

31:41.317 --> 31:43.361
(MOBILE BEEPS)

31:45.613 --> 31:47.073
(PANTING)
You've got to break
that wall down.

31:47.157 --> 31:48.992
We've got
to get in there.

31:49.075 --> 31:51.745
-Slow down. What happened?
-You were right about my dad,
about Zoe.

31:51.828 --> 31:53.830
I remembered it.

31:53.913 --> 31:55.832
I was five years old.
There was another room
up on that top corridor.

31:55.915 --> 31:59.836
And I saw my dad there
with Granddad
and a dead girl.

31:59.919 --> 32:02.172
I think Zoe might be
in there.

32:02.255 --> 32:06.426
Kate, you have to tell me
what's going on, right now,
all right?

32:06.509 --> 32:07.761
I lied to you.

32:09.095 --> 32:12.265
He was burning things.

32:14.100 --> 32:15.602
I found Zoe's necklace.

33:35.223 --> 33:37.142
-WARREN:
(SCREAMING) No!
-Keep going!

33:39.769 --> 33:41.354
(GRUNTING)

33:41.438 --> 33:43.231
WARREN:
You don't know
what you're doing!

33:43.898 --> 33:44.899
(GRUNTS)

34:08.130 --> 34:09.424
Ryan.

34:10.132 --> 34:11.509
Ryan!

34:11.592 --> 34:13.303
(SCREAMING)
Ryan! Ryan!

34:15.513 --> 34:16.723
Ryan!

34:17.223 --> 34:18.433
Ryan!

34:19.184 --> 34:21.643
-RYAN: Molly!
-Ryan!

34:21.728 --> 34:24.647
RYAN:
The door's stuck, Moll.
Push it from the inside.

34:24.731 --> 34:26.983
Right.
Hang on, I'm coming.

34:47.504 --> 34:48.505
(PANTING)

34:49.755 --> 34:50.924
Jed, what's in there?

34:51.007 --> 34:52.300
What can you see?

34:52.384 --> 34:53.677
There's nothing here.

34:54.803 --> 34:56.054
(WARREN MOANS)

35:07.565 --> 35:11.444
KATE: Jed,
what have you found?
What's happening?

35:17.784 --> 35:18.952
Jed?

35:23.623 --> 35:25.166
-Jed?
-(LIFT MOTOR WHIRRING)

35:25.250 --> 35:27.836
It was just a dream.
You're okay.

35:27.919 --> 35:30.964
You're okay,
but you have to
leave the flat.

35:31.047 --> 35:33.216
-Only if you come with me.
-I can't.

35:46.521 --> 35:49.149
Why did you just
creep out of my room
when I was sleeping?

35:51.443 --> 35:52.901
I made a mistake.

35:54.612 --> 35:57.323
Which part
was the mistake?

35:57.407 --> 35:58.992
The creeping out
or what we did before?

36:02.871 --> 36:04.789
You know what?
Don't bother.

36:04.872 --> 36:07.458
You don't have to tell me
what you were thinking.
It's obvious.

36:07.542 --> 36:11.628
"What the hell, make her
feel good. Make her think
I really want her."

36:11.713 --> 36:14.549
-I did.
-Listen to you.
You can't stop yourself!

36:14.632 --> 36:17.302
You know,
I've been screwed over
by some low lives before,

36:17.384 --> 36:19.721
but at least
they never thought
they were doing me a favour.

36:19.804 --> 36:22.598
-That's not true.
-Then why won't you
give us a chance?

36:27.520 --> 36:29.439
-What are you doing?
-I'm going to stay
with my friends.

36:29.522 --> 36:32.359
-You can't go now.
-Oh, please!

36:32.442 --> 36:34.527
I may be naive, Ryan,
but I know
what's good for me,

36:34.611 --> 36:36.404
and nothing
in this place is.

36:38.656 --> 36:39.783
It brings out
the worst in people.

36:41.201 --> 36:42.619
-Moll.
-No!

36:47.165 --> 36:48.583
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

36:57.509 --> 36:58.718
(WARREN MOANS)

37:01.513 --> 37:02.931
Oh, God.

37:18.613 --> 37:19.781
(EXHALES)

37:26.955 --> 37:28.957
(SCREAMING)

37:41.970 --> 37:43.930
(LIFT MOTOR WHIRRING)

37:44.014 --> 37:45.598
(LIFT STOPS)

37:45.682 --> 37:46.808
Jed?

37:48.560 --> 37:49.644
Jed?

37:52.272 --> 37:53.440
(SOBS)

37:53.523 --> 37:54.691
(SNIFFLES)

38:04.743 --> 38:05.910
Jed?

38:13.043 --> 38:14.794
(KATE SCREAMS)

38:14.878 --> 38:17.130
WARREN:
Get out of there.
Get out now!

38:17.213 --> 38:18.923
Why? You afraid
of what I'll find, Dad?

38:19.007 --> 38:20.550
You don't know
what's down there.

38:25.055 --> 38:26.264
(METAL CREAKS)

38:32.479 --> 38:34.522
-You lied to me.
-I didn't kill her.

38:35.899 --> 38:37.108
I burnt the things
she left behind.

38:38.068 --> 38:39.444
Why?

38:39.527 --> 38:41.363
I didn't want the police
digging around.

38:44.074 --> 38:47.994
Your granddad,
he did things
to the inmates.

38:48.078 --> 38:51.206
They were psychopaths,
child killers,
these were evil people.

38:52.624 --> 38:54.376
-You knew?
-I was scared!

38:55.377 --> 38:57.712
I was so scared.

38:57.796 --> 39:00.924
And it wasn't just him.
Where you are now,
that's where they were taken.

39:01.007 --> 39:02.509
What's down there now?

39:02.592 --> 39:04.678
-(THUMPING)
-(GASPS)

39:04.761 --> 39:07.013
What about the others?
What about Grace's daughter?

39:07.097 --> 39:08.723
I never knew about them,

39:08.807 --> 39:11.768
I swear on my life,
not until after
he had killed himself.

39:11.851 --> 39:13.019
And Zoe?

39:14.354 --> 39:16.356
She had nothing to do
with granddad.

39:19.984 --> 39:22.237
Did you take
the necklace
to the police?

39:29.577 --> 39:30.829
WARREN:
(SCREAMING) No!

39:30.912 --> 39:33.289
Kate, please,
you've got to look at me.

39:33.373 --> 39:35.458
Look at me.
You have to trust me.

39:35.542 --> 39:38.628
You think I can ever...

39:40.005 --> 39:41.381
Trust you again?

39:47.012 --> 39:48.179
(GRUNTS)

39:48.263 --> 39:49.889
(PANTING)

39:56.104 --> 39:57.230
(STRAINING)

39:57.313 --> 39:58.440
(METAL CREAKING)

40:14.539 --> 40:16.291
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)

40:29.804 --> 40:31.681
(MOBILE BEEPS)

40:50.867 --> 40:53.161
MOLLY: Bad things happened
here, and that doesn't
just go away.

40:53.244 --> 40:54.579
Zoe never came home
last night.

40:54.662 --> 40:56.456
I don't scare as easily
as I used to.

40:56.539 --> 40:58.875
I know what's good for me,
and nothing in this place is.

40:58.958 --> 41:01.086
It brings out
the worst in people.

41:01.169 --> 41:03.296
WARREN: The missing girl,
someone saw her
getting into a white van.

41:04.547 --> 41:05.674
(CAR HORN TOOTING)

41:15.934 --> 41:17.227
(KATE GRUNTS)

41:17.936 --> 41:19.145
(BREATH TREMBLING)

41:35.704 --> 41:36.913
Jed?

41:46.172 --> 41:47.298
Jed!

41:59.728 --> 42:00.729
Jed?

42:02.814 --> 42:04.441
(CREAKING)

42:04.524 --> 42:05.900
(RUMBLING)

42:07.110 --> 42:08.695
(SCREAMING)
Jed!

42:08.778 --> 42:11.322
Kate!
Kate, you have to go back.

42:11.406 --> 42:12.407
You've found her,
haven't you?

42:14.200 --> 42:16.703
No, Kate,
listen to me, all right?
You have to leave now.

42:16.786 --> 42:18.204
So, where is she?

42:18.288 --> 42:20.749
Kate, this has
got nothing to do
with Zoe, all right?

42:20.832 --> 42:22.083
Leave now.

42:22.167 --> 42:23.251
(GASPS)

42:23.335 --> 42:24.878
-(KATE SCREAMING)
-Kate!

42:24.961 --> 42:25.962
No! Jed!

42:28.923 --> 42:29.924
(SCREAMING)

42:40.393 --> 42:41.811
KATE: (SCREAMING)
No, Jed!

42:41.895 --> 42:43.897
(SOBBING) No!

42:43.980 --> 42:46.483
No! Jed!

42:46.566 --> 42:47.567
Jed!

42:58.828 --> 42:59.996
Mum.

43:03.750 --> 43:05.251
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

43:10.590 --> 43:11.925
(SCREAMING)

43:13.468 --> 43:14.803
(PANTING)

43:14.886 --> 43:15.929
(EXHALES)
